rComments: Always very passionate about the authors and she truly cared how students were progressing. I found her very approachable and helpful. Overall, one of the best profs i've had thus far.
She's excellent! Very enthusiastic. Lectures are clear and provide lots of textual examples (making it very easy come essay time).
Extremely enthusiastic and well informed prof. Really fascinating course. Always there when you need her.
Excellent prof. Lectures were very well organized. She managed to cover a lot of material in a clear way. A very engaging instructor.
Great prof! Brilliant and very helpful.

I took this class in the summer at St. George and she was the best professor.  She was extremely helpful and was willing to guide those who were not English majors (science) if we were ever confused.  She knew her material very well and taught me to appreciate some good short stories
An extremely helpful instructor who presented course material in a very clear and encouraging manner. You can tell she really cares about her students and wants them to do well.
A very intelligent instructor. Gave clear examples of how to complete assignments, and consistently provided individual feedback. Definitely worth trying to get her for an instructor.
